mlflex.core
Class DataValues

java.lang.Object
  mlflex.core.DataValues
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String>
public class DataValues
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String>, java.lang.Comparable

This class is designed to store key/value pairs and to provide convenience methods for dealing with key/value pairs.

Author:
Stephen Piccolo

AddBinaryDataPoint

public void AddBinaryDataPoint(java.lang.String name,
                               java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> values,
                               java.lang.String oneOption)
Adds a binary data point to this instance. Multiple values can be specified, and if any of them are the same as the "one option" value, the data point is marked as 1; otherwise, it is marked as 0.

Parameters:
name - Data point name
values - Data point values
oneOption - One option
